================================================================================
PART 6: CROSSOVER P_0 ANALYSIS
================================================================================

Need: C/A > |1 - D/A|
  C/A >= pi^2 / (432 * C_W * logN)
  |1 - D/A| <= K * |M(p)| / p <= K * 0.571 / sqrt(N)
  with K = 6.37 (empirical)

Crossover: sqrt(N)/logN > 432 * C_W * 3.637 / pi^2 = 159.2 * C_W

Scenario: C_W <= logN (proved)
  Formula: sqrt(N)/log^2(N) > 159.2 * C_W
  Crossover not reached for N <= 10^10

Scenario: C_W <= 1 (plausible)
  Formula: sqrt(N)/logN > 159.2 * C_W
  Crossover at N ~ 1e+07

Scenario: C_W <= 0.71 (verified to 100K)
  Formula: sqrt(N)/logN > 159.2 * C_W
  Crossover at N ~ 5e+06

