================================================================================
PART 8: STRATEGIES TO CLOSE THE PROOF
================================================================================

Strategy A: Extend computation to N ~ 10^7
  Feasibility: O(N) per prime, ~4*10^6 primes to check
  Total work: ~4*10^13 ops, ~few hours on modern hardware
  Combined with C_W <= 1: PROOF CLOSES

Strategy B: Tighten delta_sq to include composite denominators
  Current: delta_sq >= N^2/(48*logN) [primes only]
  Potential: delta_sq >= N^2/(12*logN) [all denominators, ~4x gain]
  Crossover with C_W<=1: P_0 ~ 10^5 (within current verification!)
  This is the MOST PROMISING path.

Strategy C: Prove C_W <= constant analytically
  Method: Insert Lee-Leong into Ramanujan sum expansion
  This would give C/A >= c/logN rigorously
  Required: careful explicit analytic number theory

Strategy D: Prove D/A >= 1 - c/logN (equidistribution)
  Would close proof directly with P_0 ~ 100
  Requires substantial new analytic work

